description.paragraph1: Encore is a lightweight Core Banking Solution that meets the requirements of organisations engaged in Lending.

paragraph2.text: Encore supports three types of loans:
paragraph2.listItem1: Equated installment loans - weekly, fortnightly, monthly, quarterly, half-yearly and yearly frequency supported
paragraph2.listItem2: Bullet loans with payment of principal and interest at end of term
paragraph2.listItem3: Working capital loans with ability to do disbursements and repayments repeatedly like a line of credit

paragraph3.listItem1: Disbursement with processing fees. Net and gross disbursements provided
paragraph3.listItem2: Variety of repayment methods - Scheduled repayments, advance repayments, prepayments and pre-closures
paragraph3.listItem4: Both EOD and Schedule balance methods of interest computation.
paragraph3.listItem5: Reversal and back value dating of transactions.
paragraph3.listItem6: Fees can be charged on loan transactions on both fixed and percentage basis.
paragraph3.listItem7: Trial balance reports, future projection reports are among the many reports supported.
paragraph3.listItem8: Holiday marking facility is provided when generating repayment schedules.
paragraph3.listItem9: Securitisation is available if the loans are to be pooled and sold to investors.
paragraph3.listItem10: Batch scheduling support is available for automated EOD operations of interest booking, date change and demand generation.

description.paragraph4: Current and savings accounts are provided with support for deposits, withdrawals and fund transfers. The interest computation methods include EOD balance, minimum balance and average balance methods.
description.paragraph5: The solution has been developed using Open Source Java environment with Spring, Hibernate and MySQL running on Tomcat application server. It has a low cost of ownership. It can be hosted on the cloud. Web services are provided for integration with any external origination systems.
